subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Head immaculate (
Fig. 3A
). Pronotum with median spots projected (
Fig. 3B
). Pretarsal claw (
Fig. 3E
) with basal dilation more than half length of claw hook, lateral outer margin strongly rounded. Forewing with most outer gradates black (
Fig. 3C
). Abdomen with reddish markings on terga 2–6, and marking on tergum 6 much larger. Sterna 8+9 about 2.5 times as long as wide (
Fig. 4B
). Apical invagination of sterna 8+9 deep. Tignum narrow (
Fig. 4D
); gonarcus very narrow (
Fig. 4C
); entoprocessus rounded, not curved inward apically (
Fig. 4C
).

Head (
Fig. 1A
): Vertex and frons pale green, immaculate; gena and tentorial unmarked; scape unmarked; clypeus and labrum unmarked; maxillary palp and labial palp pale green.

Thorax (
Fig. 1B
): Almost pale green. Pronotum with median oval spots projected. Pretarsal claw (
Fig. 3E
) with basal dilation more than half length of claw hook, lateral outer margin strongly rounded.

Wings (
Figs 1C, 1D
): Forewing moderately narrow, hyaline. Radial crossvein at junction with R, the first and median radial crossveins and most outer gradates black; first intramedian cell long and narrow, ovate; gradates in two rows; inner gradates pale green; hind wing narrow, more acutely tapering apically than forewing, hyaline; veins pale green; gradates in two rows.

Male (
Fig. 2
): T9+ectoprocts short, about half as tergum 8; callus cerci oval, about twice as long as wide. Sterna 8+9 fused, moderately narrow, about 2.5 times as long as wide, with line of fusion not demarcated; lateral margin slightly tapered, posterior margin strongly invaginated. Tignum present, projected medially; gonarcus very narrow, about 2/3 length of mediuncus; entoprocessus rounded and not curved inward apically; mediuncus trilobed, with lateral lobe strongly curved in lateral view, about 2/3 length of ventral median lobe.

